You are implementing a composition manifest module (`app/api/pipeline/_lib/composition-manifest.ts`) for a video production pipeline. This module manages a JSON manifest that tracks generated Remotion composition metadata per section.

Role: Provide CRUD helpers and staleness detection for the composition manifest stored at `{projectDir}/outputs/compositions/manifest.json`.

Requirements
1. Export types: `GeneratedCompositionManifestSection` (id, compositionId, optional specDir, optional timelineSource, compositions array from `Section["compositions"]`). Internal manifest type has `version: 1`, `updatedAt` ISO string, optional `generatorFingerprint`, and sections array.
2. Export `CompositionArtifactState` type with `stale: boolean`, `manifestFingerprint: string | null`, `currentFingerprint: string`, `reason: "generator_changed" | "missing_manifest_fingerprint" | null`.
3. `getCompositionGeneratorFingerprint()` — SHA-256 hash of a versioned salt (`composition-generator-v{N}`) plus the content of key generator input files: `generate_section_compositions.py`, `composition-timing.ts`, `spec-timestamp.ts`, `section-timing.ts`, `visual-contract-manifest.ts`, `visual-runtime.tsx`. Skip missing files. Hash includes relative paths.
4. `getCompositionManifestPath(projectDir?)` — returns `{projectDir}/outputs/compositions/manifest.json`.
5. `loadCompositionManifest(projectDir?)` — reads and parses the manifest JSON. Returns `null` if missing, unparseable, or structurally invalid (must have `sections` array and `updatedAt` string).
6. `mergeCompositionManifest(sections, projectDir?)` — merges incoming sections into existing manifest by `id` (upsert), stamps `updatedAt` and `generatorFingerprint`, writes atomically with `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })`.
7. `getCompositionArtifactState(projectDir?)` — returns staleness info. No manifest → not stale. Manifest without fingerprint → stale with reason `"missing_manifest_fingerprint"`. Fingerprint mismatch → stale with reason `"generator_changed"`.
8. `isCompositionArtifactSetStale(projectDir?)` — boolean convenience wrapper around `getCompositionArtifactState`.
9. `resolveSectionGeneratedMetadata(section)` — looks up a section by `id` in the default manifest.
10. `resolveSectionCompositionIds(section)` — resolves composition entries (manifest-first, fallback to `section.compositions`), extracts string IDs, filters nullish.

